-- Calpers Commodity Holdings Fell 0.7% in December to $1.577B
-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   C a m p b e l l
-- 2013-02-19T15:43:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-19/calpers-commodity-holdings-fell-0-7-in-december-to-1-577b.html
The value of commodity holdings by
the California Public Employees’ Retirement System, the largest
U.S. pension fund, fell 0.7 percent in December from the
previous month, according to the most-recent data available.  The fund held $1.577 billion in commodities as of Dec. 31,
or 0.6 percent of the total assets listed at $248.775 billion,
according to a monthly  report  on  today ’s agenda for the fund’s
investment committee meeting. That’s down from $1.588 billion as
of  Nov. 30 , or 0.7 percent of total assets of $243.669 billion.
In October, the fund reduced its commodity holdings by 55
percent, after reporting $3.45 billion as of Sept. 30.  The fund’s board is meeting today, tomorrow and Feb. 21,
according to Calper’s  website .  To contact the reporter on this story:
